reviews.review_text: class act check out joe's other recordings.  like this one, they are very good.  this performance is also excellent.
Fair But Good Highlights: Playing Jam

Best Version This is the best sounding version of this show.  I was there, all of 18 years old.  28 downbeats on the BIODTL for the date of the show.  Listen closely to the Iko, Loser, and Althea for your most amazing Bobby guitar licks during the Garcia solos.  Just great bwangs and reverb-soaked reactions. Some of the best Bobby stuff ever. Also check out the "Looks Like Rain" from the Providence run of this tour for the best version ever.
